    verification headlessSyncRetroGate : Test { :>> id = "a44d5fa0-a143-4616-a8d0-3364aa577016"; :>> title = "Sprint 14 retro gate (autonomous, D0049)"; :>> createdAt = "2026-07-02"; :>> createdBy = "ai"; :>> method = VerificationMethod::analyze; :>> procedureText = "Autonomous retro (D0049). WELL: dPlugins' native-reimplementation call paid off - a small ServerPlugin trait + an injected CliRunner made a CLI-dependent feature fully unit-testable without the CLI; wiring the ChannelHub closed the sprint06 subscribe-channel loose end for free. AVOIDABLE-ISSUE SCAN: no new tracked issues - the faked-CLI test coverage is an accepted, unavoidable limit (no obsidian-headless in the env); a couple of sync-state fields were inferred. PROCESS NOTE (recurring): a fork again stopped after backgrounding a slow compile without reporting - a finish-check (test+clippy+wiring) before closing is now standard for these. LESSON: inject external-process dependencies behind a trait so the happy path is testable + the real binary is a deploy concern. Estimate 8pt held."; }
    part headlessSyncRetroGateR1 : TestResult { :>> id = "2cd437c2-fe39-4851-97c0-4179123f9670"; :>> outcome = VerdictKind::pass; :>> judgedAgainst = "ceca03b"; :>> judgedAt = "2026-07-02"; :>> judgedBy = "ai"; }
